feet, but here they're in the arms and legs.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057437,0.10155,0.10967,0.11626,0.10595,0.09601,0.090504,0.081677,0.073599,0.063744,0.056113,0.04749],"unified_progress":[0.053784,0.090466,0.10369,0.10996,0.10907,0.1009,0.095281,0.088604,0.083611,0.069956,0.055465,0.039221]},{"section":5,"text":"The cranial nerves are normal, so facial muscles and eye movements are okay, which suggests the issue isn't in the brain or the cranial nerves themselves.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04811,0.08532,0.10009,0.10992,0.10485,0.099373,0.096158,0.087864,0.080441,0.071365,0.062703,0.05381],"unified_progress":[0.042056,0.075725,0.093325,0.1032,0.10673,0.10396,0.10035,0.093982,0.090868,0.077811,0.063495,0.048498]},{"section":6,"text":"He has weakness specifically in his left handgrip and right leg quadriceps.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051864,0.092029,0.093512,0.093238,0.096268,0.094191,0.093586,0.089153,0.084191,0.076047,0.071634,0.064287],"unified_progress":[0.051995,0.083422,0.092454,0.098424,0.10121,0.10308,0.09737,0.093133,0.08815,0.077107,0.063474,0.050189]},{"section":7,"text":"So, grip weakness in the left hand and quadriceps weakness in the right leg.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043559,0.074056,0.087371,0.092621,0.098202,0.097968,0.098481,0.094793,0.090376,0.081916,0.074893,0.065765],"unified_progress":[0.044387,0.075374,0.091091,0.099196,0.10275,0.10574,0.099745,0.094664,0.092104,0.078938,0.064716,0.051294]},{"section":8,"text":"That's interesting because it's not symmetric.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035646,0.11753,0.13008,0.1475,0.10693,0.091834,0.082748,0.073952,0.06346,0.05752,0.049339,0.043466],"unified_progress":[0.026006,0.069834,0.092536,0.10734,0.1064,0.10208,0.10752,0.10131,0.094139,0.086499,0.066015,0.04033]},{"section":9,"text":"Also, there's loss of muscle bulk, which makes me think of muscle wasting, often seen in conditions affecting motor neurons.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042099,0.084664,0.099614,0.11282,0.10483,0.099924,0.096273,0.090188,0.082623,0.073581,0.062605,0.050775],"unified_progress":[0.034271,0.066773,0.084674,0.096377,0.10147,0.10329,0.10466,0.10212,0.09579,0.090183,0.07122,0.049171]},{"section":10,"text":"Tone is increased in the arms and legs, and reflexes are brisk.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03871,0.075709,0.096083,0.10083,0.10316,0.09957,0.096831,0.09126,0.085726,0.077856,0.071901,0.062366],"unified_progress":[0.048836,0.081462,0.091461,0.097078,0.10128,0.10143,0.09847,0.095486,0.089776,0.080404,0.065756,0.04856]},{"section":11,"text":"Increased tone and brisk reflexes can be signs of upper motor neuron lesions.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033739,0.061464,0.080562,0.09108,0.098545,0.10116,0.1033,0.10158,0.09773,0.088689,0.078283,0.063872],"unified_progress":[0.042079,0.070475,0.085903,0.093691,0.099078,0.10411,0.10068,0.098994,0.094415,0.088031,0.070877,0.051668]},{"section":12,"text":"Upper motor neurons are responsible for sending signals from the brain to the spinal cord, so if they're affected, you get things like spasticity and hyperreflexia.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036758,0.059698,0.076606,0.087764,0.096175,0.10008,0.10435,0.10354,0.10004,0.091096,0.079209,0.064675],"unified_progress":[0.036139,0.063953,0.083099,0.093789,0.10063,0.10516,0.10283,0.10023,0.098065,0.089162,0.073183,0.053757]},{"section":13,"text":"Putting this together: weakness with fasciculations, muscle wasting, increased tone, and brisk reflexes.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039503,0.076789,0.078054,0.075363,0.081345,0.083132,0.086602,0.089875,0.089931,0.086445,0.10217,0.11079],"unified_progress":[0.079292,0.11088,0.094143,0.086809,0.085057,0.085631,0.082496,0.085996,0.079767,0.074862,0.070331,0.06474]},{"section":14,"text":"These are classic signs of a motor neuron disease.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035852,0.089524,0.098908,0.11014,0.092169,0.086195,0.08441,0.082505,0.079067,0.078999,0.07902,0.083216],"unified_progress":[0.034196,0.069064,0.089259,0.10267,0.096419,0.094934,0.097302,0.093595,0.089841,0.086269,0.078552,0.067902]},{"section":15,"text":"Now, motor neuron diseases can be various, like amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), spinal muscular atrophy, or others.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027827,0.054673,0.070856,0.082468,0.095914,0.10154,0.11075,0.11194,0.10394,0.094503,0.079251,0.066338],"unified_progress":[0.027315,0.056379,0.080364,0.094303,0.10154,0.11054,0.10986,0.10548,0.098698,0.090303,0.072169,0.05305]},{"section":16,"text":"But given the distribution and the presence of both upper and lower motor neuron signs, ALS comes to mind.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034862,0.053056,0.068,0.077847,0.087649,0.093271,0.098894,0.1015,0.10187,0.1004,0.094543,0.088111],"unified_progress":[0.033124,0.056036,0.070428,0.081642,0.089267,0.096715,0.096697,0.10052,0.099765,0.099911,0.092179,0.083714]},{"section":17,"text":"In ALS, you typically see both upper (like hyperreflexia) and lower motor neuron signs (fasciculations, weakness, muscle wasting).","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031563,0.054337,0.067979,0.077,0.087895,0.094031,0.10098,0.10429,0.10399,0.098053,0.094272,0.085607],"unified_progress":[0.044228,0.071025,0.079921,0.08613,0.091837,0.097949,0.097018,0.098467,0.095895,0.091827,0.080413,0.065289]},{"section":18,"text":"The asymmetry in weakness might be early in the disease, as ALS can start in one limb and spread.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033358,0.053335,0.069377,0.